Loicque Hi,

I said I'd get back to you on this.

To be able to assess the figures, we've requested and received a proposal
from Safra bank, with whom Eran has a working relationship and whom he
recommends.

They came back with the following rates:

For a/c above 2.5m USD

Annual a/c maintenance fee: 500

Custody fee pa:             0.10%

Tx fee for Equities/=E2=80=A6:      0.10%

Tx fee for Bonds:           0.10%

Tx fee for HD/ PE Funds:    0.25%

Coupon Dividends Waived

Annual Tax report:          200


As much as we'd like to continue working with HSBC, I'm having a hard time
justifying to myself the three- to four-fold difference in fees. Granted,
after a period of trading, the majority of fees might settle on the custody
line item, but still...


Could you please take another look to see if you can improve the offer?


Thanks,


Adam



On Fri, 1 Nov 2019 at 12:26, Loicque WINDEY <loicque.windey@hsbcpb.com>
wrote:

